    1. java (JDK 1.8)
    2. wireless Tool kit 2.5
  Development 
    1.java class extends MIDLet -- it contains life cycle methods
    2.Display -- > Forms ---> Components 
    3.event handling 
        1.CommandListener     -->   public void commandAction(Command command, Displayable displayable)
        2.ItemStateListener   -->   public void itemStateChanged(Item item) 

2. Android -- open source (OS)
    1. SDK -- > software devlopment kit
    2. Gradle -->   Build Tool
    3. .apk --> android packing 
    4. manifest -->  Agrement between android application and os
    5. Ativity  -- > it contatins Business Logic(functionality)
       layout --> Collection of view (Content to be displayed on screen)
    6. res -- > resources values,drawables,minmap,layouts
    7. drawables -- > contains all images in application
    8. values (folder) --> strings , color, styles
    9. constraint:  ,Linear: orintation , grid : num row .. ,table : row, relative : layout_above ..  
    10 AVD  -- > Android Virtual Device 

